</p>
<p>Great, now we can access Symfony's DependencyInjection classes and a few other
libraries we'll use, like Monolog.</p>
<h2 id="using-monolog-straight-up">Using Monolog Straight-Up <a class="headerlink" href="container-in-the-wild#using-monolog-straight-up" title="Permalink to this headline"><i class="fa fa-link" aria-hidden="true"></i></a></h2>
<p>In fact, forget about containers and Symfony and all that weird stuff. Let's
<em>just</em> use the Monolog library to log some stuff. That's simple, just
<code>$logger = new Logger()</code>. The first argument is the channel - it's like a
category - you'll see that word <code>main</code> in the logs. Now log something:
<code>$logger-&gt;info()</code>, then ROOOAR:</p>
<p><div class="code-block-wrapper" data-code-block-guid="bc66394fa9">
    <div class="meta">
        <div class="actions">
            <span class="fa fa-clipboard js-activate-clipboard" data-toggle="tooltip" title="Copy Code" data-placement="top"></span>
        </div>
        <div class="info">
